Dear Tom:<br><br>
Certainly, your pristine values must be assailed with greater frequency and intensity than most of your &quot;rough shod&quot; pals... including me.<br>
Your incredible values were not prostituted by a horrible war, but were put into bronze.  You are the light on the hill for many who are confused by anger and hatred.. leading them to the foot of the Cross where they can and may cast away a portion, if not all, of the burdens of war.<br>
While your moral fiber is intact, your human fiber is a little frayed by the antics of those you love and hope for. It is not outside the realm of possibility that you are lacking in trust of mortals or that your patience has grown thin.  Trust and innocence are two essential ingredients in dealing with the transfer of wisdom.. first from God and then.. imparting those findings to others in need.  Our trust has been fractured and a large portion of our innocence has been trodden into the blood and mud of Vietnam.<br>
Satan is an imposter.. no big secret, huh!  He uses mortals to purvey his anti-wisdom (wrong directions).. no big secret, huh?  I have a feeling that you will never stop combating that which is counter to goodness and the welfare of humanity.<br>
As your concerned brother, I am sensitive to the fact that implosive flooding.. desensitization.. is necessary for emotional healing. But, we must be careful not gain new wounds or drown in the huge waves that occassionally roll over us.<br>
I will suffer your departure, if only you are gone one day, but I will rejoice at your return.<br>
In the meantime, we'll clear a spot for you to stretch your poncho and keep a can of C's hot for you.  We'll keep an eye on the back trail.. anticipating your early return.<br><br>
Your Brother in Arms.. your Friend in Jesus,<br><br>
